t: Deuteronomy 23
He*p that is wounded in the stones, or hath his privy member cut off, shall not enter into the congregation of the Lord.*s
A*p bastard shall not enter into the congregation of the Lord;*s even to his tenth generation shall he not enter into the congregation of the Lord.*s
An*p Ammonite or Moabite shall not enter into the congregation of the Lord;*s even to their tenth generation shall they not enter into the congregation of the Lord*s for ever:
Because*p they met you not with bread and with water in the way, when ye came forth out of Egypt; and because they hired against thee Balaam the son of Beor of Pethor of Mesopotamia, to curse thee.
Nevertheless*p the Lord*s thy God would not hearken unto Balaam; but the Lord*s thy God turned the curse into a blessing unto thee, because the Lord*s thy God loved thee.
Thou*p shalt not seek their peace nor their prosperity all thy days for ever.
Thou*p shalt not abhor an Edomite; for he is thy brother: thou shalt not abhor an Egyptian; because thou wast a stranger in his land.
The*p children that are begotten of them shall enter into the congregation of the Lord*s in their third generation.
When*p the host goeth forth against thine enemies, then keep thee from every wicked thing.
If*p there be among you any man, that is not clean by reason of uncleanness that chanceth him by night, then shall he go abroad out of the camp, he shall not come within the camp:
But*p it shall be, when evening cometh on, he shall wash himself with water: and when the sun is down, he shall come into the camp again.
Thou*p shalt have a place also without the camp, whither thou shalt go forth abroad:
And*p thou shalt have a paddle upon thy weapon; and it shall be, when thou wilt ease thyself abroad, thou shalt dig therewith, and shalt turn back and cover that which cometh from thee:

Thou*p shalt not deliver unto his master the servant which is escaped from his master unto thee:

There*p shall be no whore of the daughters of Israel, nor a sodomite of the sons of Israel.
Thou*p shalt not bring the hire of a whore, or the price of a dog, into the house of the Lord*s thy God for any vow: for even both these are abomination unto the Lord*s thy God.
Thou*p shalt not lend upon usury to thy brother; usury of money, usury of victuals, usury of any thing that is lent upon usury:

Unto*p a stranger thou mayest lend upon usury; but unto thy brother thou shalt not lend upon usury: that the Lord*s thy God may bless thee in all that thou settest thine hand to in the land whither thou goest to possess it.

When*p thou comest into thy neighbour's vineyard, then thou mayest eat grapes thy fill at thine own pleasure; but thou shalt not put any in thy vessel.
When*p thou comest into the standing corn of thy neighbour, then thou mayest pluck the ears with thine hand; but thou shalt not move a sickle unto thy neighbour's standing corn.
